The paper deals with the computational complexity of a combinatorial optimization problem, which is a central topic in theoretical computer science. The problem is related to constraint satisfaction problems and valued constraint satisfaction problems, which are typically studied in the areas of computational complexity (cs.CC), algorithms (cs.DS), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), logic in computer science (cs.LO), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
